Architecture plan for issues #69-#73

Project shape
- alex-0d18-test-20 is a Node/TypeScript monorepo with npm workspaces.
- frontend/: Vite + React + React Router + Tailwind CSS. Theme work should stay in frontend configuration, CSS, contexts, and shared shell components.
- backend/: Express + TypeScript + Prisma. These issues do not require backend or database changes.

Module structure and file organization
- frontend/tailwind.config.js:
  - Extend theme.colors.app with semantic tokens backed by CSS variables.
  - Extend fontFamily.sans with the Inter-first stack.
- frontend/src/styles.css:
  - Define default emerald `--app-*` CSS variables on `:root`.
  - Add `:root[data-theme="indigo"]`, `rose`, and `amber` overrides for accent-related variables.
  - Apply global body background/text through the semantic variables.
- frontend/src/contexts/theme.tsx:
  - Export `ColorTheme`, `colorThemes`, `ThemeProvider`, and `useTheme`.
  - Persist selected theme in `localStorage` under `app_color_theme`.
  - Write `document.documentElement.dataset.theme` from the provider.
- frontend/src/main.tsx:
  - Wrap the current app tree as `BrowserRouter > ThemeProvider > AuthProvider > App`.
- frontend/src/App.tsx:
  - Add a compact header `ColorSettings` swatch control.
  - Migrate the app shell, header, navigation, buttons, user summary, and empty/error route cards to `app.*` semantic Tailwind classes.
- frontend/src/components and frontend/src/pages:
  - Replace remaining hardcoded `zinc-*`, `emerald-*`, and `white` presentation classes with the appropriate `app.*` semantic classes.

Shared types and conventions
- `ColorTheme` should be the union `"emerald" | "indigo" | "rose" | "amber"`.
- `colorThemes` should be the single source for labels and swatch hex values used by the header picker.
- Semantic color classes should describe UI role, not palette name: `bg-app-bg`, `bg-app-surface`, `bg-app-surfaceMuted`, `text-app-text`, `text-app-muted`, `border-app-border`, `bg-app-accentSoft`, `text-app-accentText`, `focus:ring-app-ring`.

Issue dependencies and order
- #69 goes first because Tailwind tokens and CSS variables are the foundation.
- #70 depends on #69 and introduces persisted runtime theme selection.
- #71 depends on #70 and exposes the theme selector in the header.
- #72 depends on #71 and migrates App.tsx shell/navigation/button styles to semantic tokens.
- #73 depends on #72 and finishes the remaining component/page color migration, then verifies the workspace build.

Key design decisions
- Keep this as a frontend-only batch; no backend, Prisma, auth, storage, or API behavior changes are needed.
- Preserve layout and routes while changing color sources.
- Use CSS variables for palette changes so Tailwind class names remain stable across themes.
- Persist only the user's theme choice in browser localStorage; no provisioned database or object storage is needed for this batch.
- Treat the emerald theme as the default with indigo, rose, and amber overriding only the accent series requested by the issues.
- Run `npm run build --workspaces --if-present` after the final migration issue to catch Tailwind/config regressions.
